We will build a Linear regression model for Medical cost dataset. The dataset consists of age, sex, BMI(body mass index), children, smoker and region feature, which are independent and charge as a dependent feature. We will predict individual medical costs billed by health insurance.

In [30]:
# encoding sex column
insurance_dataset.replace({'sex':{'male':0,'female':1}}, inplace=True)

3 # encoding 'smoker' column
insurance_dataset.replace({'smoker':{'yes':0,'no':1}}, inplace=True)

# encoding 'region' column
insurance_dataset.replace({'region':{'southeast':0,'southwest':1,'northeast':2,'northwest':3}}, inplace=True)

Splitting the Features and Target

In [31]:
X = insurance_dataset.drop(columns='charges', axis=1)

In [42]:
from sklearn import metrics
meanAbErr = metrics.mean_absolute_error(Y_test, Y_prediction)
meanSqErr = metrics.mean_squared_error(Y_test, Y_prediction)
rootMeanSqErr = np.sqrt(metrics.mean_squared_error(Y_test, Y_prediction))
r2_test = metrics.r2_score(Y_test, Y_prediction)
print('Mean Absolute Error:', meanAbErr)
print('Mean Square Error:', meanSqErr)
print('Root Mean Square Error:', rootMeanSqErr)
print('R squared vale : ', r2_test)

Mean Absolute Error: 4251.180538000687
Mean Square Error: 37804245.53227782
Root Mean Square Error: 6148.515717819856
R squared vale :  0.766118606810119

The Multiple Linear Regression model performs well as 77% of the data fit the regression model. Also, the mean absolute error, mean square error, and the root mean square error are less.

In [43]:
# Check for Linearity
f = plt.figure(figsize=(14,5))
ax = f.add_subplot(121)
sns.scatterplot(Y_test,Y_prediction,ax=ax,color='r')
ax.set_title('Check for Linearity:\n Actual Vs Predicted value')

# Check for Residual normality & mean
ax = f.add_subplot(122)
sns.distplot((Y_test - Y_prediction),ax=ax,color='b')
ax.axvline((Y_test - Y_prediction).mean(),color='k',linestyle='--')
ax.set_title('Check for Residual normality & mean: \n Residual eror');

In our model the actual vs predicted plot is curve so linear assumption fails The residual mean is zero and residual error plot right skewed
